# Creating components

- Always wrap components in Readonly
- Do not use `React` namespace, just use named exports (e.g., use `ReactNode` instead of `React.ReactNode`, `ComponentProps` instead of `React.ComponentProps`)
- Always use `PropsWithChildren` react type util when declaring children prop
- For HTML element props, use `ComponentProps<'element'>` pattern (e.g., `ComponentProps<'input'>`, `ComponentProps<'button'>`)
- Prefer inline export instead of exporting at the end of the file
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces for component props when extending HTML elements
- Always destructure props with proper typing in function parameters
- Use `cn` utility for className merging when combining multiple classes